image_analysis.description: A page from a printed book or report containing four photographs and accompanying descriptive text. The photographs include two social event photos of Jeffrey Epstein, one booking photo (mugshot) of Epstein, and one aerial photograph of a detention facility. One person's face in the middle-left photograph is redacted with a black box.
image_analysis.layout: Multi-column layout with text wrapping around four distinct images. The page appears to be part of a bound volume, showing the curve of the binding on the left.

The Stockade, where Epstein
served his sentence, photographed
here in 2006, was located at 673
Fairgrounds Road in West Palm
Beach, Florida. At the time, it was
used as a minimum- and medium-

juveniles, as well as male inmates
on a work-release program. (Smith
Aerial Photos)
